muscle mass—is a key phenotypic determinant of cardiometabolic 
health (1–3). Adipose tissue functions as an active endocrine organ; 
expansion of visceral fat is often accompanied by adipocyte hypertro-
phy and dysfunction, which can disrupt adiponectin–leptin signaling 
and activate pro-inflammatory pathways, thereby reducing insulin 
sensitivity and impairing vascular endothelial function (4–7). Notably, 
insulin resistance and related cardiometabolic diseases are multifacto-
